<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/444> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #444" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.52.4; Diod. 13.68.1; Chr. 354 (Mugiliano et Rutillo); Fast. Hyd. (Mugilano et Rutilio), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 98, 378f. A period of famine and pestilence (Liv. 4.52.5-8).{77}" ;
	dprr:hasID 444 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/443> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #443" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Livy Papirius has the cognomen Atratinus, but the cognomen Mugillanus in the late Fasti indicates that it was the one in Fast. Cap. In Livy and Cassiod. Nautius bears the praenomen C., but Diod. has Spurius, which is supported by the praenomen in Fast. Cap. on 419 and 404, and that in Livy and Diod. in 416, when Papirius was his colleague. See Münzer, RE." ;
	dprr:hasID 443 .
